:: StoryStart
The air tastes of metal and cinder. You are the Wanderer, your past a scar on the wasteland, your future a path unwalked. An ash storm brews on the horizon. Ahead lies the husk of an old-world relay station, a potential shelter.
[[Enter the station->RelayStationRuins]]

:: RelayStationRuins
The relay station is a skeleton of rusted steel. Inside, the wind howls through shattered windows. A glint of plastic catches your eye under a collapsed desk: a burned map fragment. Before you can take it, a raider patrol storms in.
[[Grab the fragment and flee->AshStormEscape]]
[[Hide and wait for an opening->RelayStationAmbush]]

:: AshStormEscape
You snatch the fragment as raider shouts echo. You burst out the back as the storm hits in full force, a wall of grey fury that blinds and deafens. Survival is now a race against the choking ash.
[[Push forward into the storm->StormPathAlone]]
:: RelayStationAmbush
You press into the shadows as raiders loot the main room. One of them finds the map fragment, arguing with his comrades. In the confusion, you have a chance.
[[Strike from the shadows->AmbushStealth-MapFragment1]]
[[Create a distraction->AmbushDistraction]]

:: AmbushDistraction
You knock a loose pipe from the wall, creating a clatter in an adjacent room. Two raiders investigate, leaving the one with the fragment momentarily alone.
[[Disarm the raider->AmbushStealth-MapFragment1]]
[[Attempt to sneak past->AmbushSneakFail]]

:: AmbushSneakFail
You move too quickly. The lone raider spins around, his weapon raised. There is no time to react. The shot echoes in the ruined station.
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: AmbushStealth-MapFragment1
You move like a ghost, disabling the raider before he can cry out. The map fragment is yours. The storm outside is now a blessing, masking your escape into the raging ash.
[[Seek shelter->CanyonShelter-MapFragment1]]
:: CanyonShelter-MapFragment1
You find a narrow fissure in the canyon wall, shielding you from the worst of the storm. The fragment shows a location labeled "Haven-0" and hints at three others. As the wind dies, you hear the creak of a wind-driven craft approaching.
[[Prepare for a possible threat->CanyonApproach-MapFragment1]]
[[Remain hidden->CanyonHide-MapFragment1]]
:: CanyonApproach-MapFragment1
A young courier, whom you later learn is called Moth, steps from the lightweight craft. She eyes you cautiously but without hostility. "The storm is fierce. The Dustborn offer shelter, if you seek it."
[[Accept the offer->NomadCaravan-MapFragment1]]
[[Decline politely->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]
:: CanyonHide-MapFragment1
You watch from the shadows as the courier, Moth, scans the canyon. Finding nothing, she departs. You are alone again with the map.
[[Continue your journey->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]

:: WastesAlone-MapFragment1
The wastes stretch endlessly. Your path leads towards a rumor: a trading outpost called Rusthaven. It is a den of information and danger.
[[Travel to Rusthaven->RusthavenGates-MapFragment1]]
:: NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-WithMoth
Moth's land-sailer glides over the ash. The Dustborn caravan is a mobile village of tents and crafts. They are curious about the outsider, and Moth vouches for you. An elder speaks of other fragments.
[[Ask for directions to the Union->NomadToUnionPath-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
[[Head towards the Legion-controlled territory->RoadToFortress-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
[[Strike out on your own from the caravan->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]
:: RusthavenGates-MapFragment1
Rusthaven's gates are crude scrap metal. Guards eye you. Inside, the air is thick with smoke and deals. A commotion erupts near a makeshift arena.
[[Intervene on the exile's behalf->RusthavenFight-LyraRescued-MapFragment1]]
[[Stay out of it->RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1]]
:: RusthavenFight-LyraRescued-MapFragment1
You disrupt the Legion's attempt to capture Lyra. She is a sharp-faced woman with eyes that see too much. "I owe you," she says, "They want my knowledge. I can help read that map you're trying so hard to hide."
[[Accept her help->RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Refuse her offer->RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1]]

:: RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1
In a quiet alley, you examine the fragment. Its encryption is complex. You need a specialist or a clue to the next piece.
[[Inquire about the Technic Union at the tavern->TavernRumors-MapFragment1]]
[[Seek out Legion contacts, risking a deal->LegionInformant-MapFragment1]]

:: RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1-WithLyra
Lyra studies the fragment in the dim light. "Haven-0... This is old-world geo-engineering. The second fragment is likely in a data vault beneath the Skybreaker ruins. But the Legion is digging there too."
[[Plan an expedition to Skybreaker->SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Search for other leads first->TavernRumors-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: TavernRumors-MapFragment1
The tavern is a roar of voices. A drunk miner slurs about "singing metal" in the deep mines, a sign of Union activity. It's a vague lead, but it's something.
[[Investigate the mines->DeepMinesEntrance-MapFragment1]]

:: TavernRumors-MapFragment1-WithLyra
Lyra listens intently. "The mines are a dead end. The 'singing metal' is just unstable strata. The Skybreaker lead is the only solid one. The Legion will secure it within days."
[[Trust Lyra's judgment->SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Investigate the mines anyway->DeepMinesEntrance-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: LegionInformant-MapFragment1
A Legion informant agrees to talk for a price. He confirms the Skybreaker site and warns that Captain Bronn Hale himself is leading the operation. The information feels like a trap.
[[Avoid Skybreaker, seek the Nomads->NomadCaravan-MapFragment1]]
[[Go to Skybreaker, prepared for a fight->SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1]]

:: DeepMinesEntrance-MapFragment1
The mine entrance is collapsed and unstable. venturing inside seems incredibly dangerous.
[[Risk the tunnel collapse->MinesCollapse-MapFragment1]]
[[Turn back->RusthavenAlley-MapFragment1]]

:: DeepMinesEntrance-MapFragment1-WithLyra
"The structure is compromised," Lyra states flatly. "Going in is suicide." She points to distant plumes of smoke on the horizon. "That is the Legion at Skybreaker. Our destination."
[[Heed her warning->SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Enter the mine against her advice->MinesCollapse-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: MinesCollapse-MapFragment1
You squeeze through a narrow gap. A deep rumble shakes the mountain, and the tunnel gives way. There is no escape.
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: MinesCollapse-MapFragment1-WithLyra
You ignore Lyra and enter the mine. She follows reluctantly. A deep rumble shakes the mountain. "I told you!" she shouts as the ceiling collapses, trapping you both.
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1
The Skybreaker ruins are a forest of broken skyscrapers. Legion airships hover over a central dig site. Getting close will require stealth or force.
[[Attempt to sneak through the outer ruins->SkybreakerOutskirts-MapFragment1]]
[[Create a diversion to draw troops away->SkybreakerDiversion-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerApproach-MapFragment1-WithLyra
"The main entrance is a death sentence," Lyra whispers. "I know a service tunnel from the old transit system. It should lead us below the Legion's position."
[[Take the service tunnel->SkybreakerSublevel1-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Ignore her and approach from above->SkybreakerOutskirts-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: SkybreakerOutskirts-MapFragment1
You navigate through shattered buildings, avoiding patrols. You see the entrance to the main facility, heavily guarded.
[[Wait for a shift change->SkybreakerWait-MapFragment1]]
[[Look for an alternative route->SkybreakerVent-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerOutskirts-MapFragment1-WithLyra
You climb a precarious tower for a better view. Lyra points to a ventilation shaft on a lower level. "That's our way in. The tunnel I mentioned is closer to ground level."
[[Descend to the service tunnel->SkybreakerSublevel1-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]
[[Try the ventilation shaft->SkybreakerVent-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: SkybreakerDiversion-MapFragment1
You start a fire in a ruined warehouse on the perimeter. Legion troops scramble to respond, thinning the guards at the main entrance.
[[Rush the entrance->SkybreakerEntrance-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerWait-MapFragment1
Patience pays off. A patrol moves out, leaving a brief window. You slip towards the facility entrance.
[[Enter the facility->SkybreakerEntrance-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerVent-MapFragment1
The ventilation shaft is a tight, dark crawl. It leads deep into the facility, emerging into a silent, dusty corridor.
[[Explore the corridor->SkybreakerSublevel2-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerVent-MapFragment1-WithLyra
The vent is cramped but passable. It deposits you in a dark maintenance hallway. Lyra checks a flickering wall terminal. "We're in the sublevel archives. The data vault should be nearby."
[[Proceed to the archives->SkybreakerSublevel2-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: SkybreakerEntrance-MapFragment1
The entrance hall is grand but ruined. A Legion squad is waiting in ambush. You walked right into it.
[[Fight your way through->SkybreakerEntranceFight-MapFragment1]]
[[Surrender->LegionCapture-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerEntranceFight-MapFragment1
The fight is fierce, but you are outnumbered. Legion reinforcements arrive, cutting off your retreat.
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: LegionCapture-MapFragment1
You are disarmed and dragged before Captain Bronn Hale. He takes your map fragment. "Haven-0 will be a Legion asset. You are no longer required."
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: SkybreakerSublevel1-MapFragment1-WithLyra
The service tunnel is damp but clear. It ends at a heavy door. Lyra bypasses the old lock. Inside is a network of corridors, untouched by the Legion above.
[[Search for the data vault->SkybreakerSublevel2-MapFragment1-WithLyra]]

:: SkybreakerSublevel2-MapFragment1
The corridor is lined with broken server racks. At the end is a sealed door marked "Geo-Data Vault." It is locked tight.
[[Try to force the door->VaultDoorFail-MapFragment1]]
[[Search for a keycard or terminal->SearchSublevel2-MapFragment1]]

:: SkybreakerSublevel2-MapFragment1-WithLyra
Lyra goes straight to a terminal beside the vault door. "The encryption is military grade, but brittle with age." After a tense minute, the door hisses open. Inside, a data crystal glows on a pedestal: the second fragment.
[[Take the fragment->SkybreakerVault-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: SearchSublevel2-MapFragment1
You find a skeleton in an office, an old keycard clutched in its hand. It might work on the vault door.
[[Use the keycard->SkybreakerVault-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]

:: VaultDoorFail-MapFragment1
The door doesn't budge. The noise attracts a Legion patrol from a connecting hallway. You are cornered.
[[->Ending-Dead]]

:: SkybreakerVault-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The vault is cold. The second map fragment is here, a data crystal. As you take it, alarms blare. The Legion has breached the sublevel.
[[Escape through a maintenance shaft->SkybreakerEscape-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]

:: SkybreakerVault-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
Lyra grabs the crystal. "We have what we came for. Now we run." She leads you to a hidden elevator shaft that ascends to the surface far from the dig site.
[[Escape to the surface->WastesEscape-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: SkybreakerEscape-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
You scramble up the shaft, emerging on the edge of the ruins. Legion patrols are swarming below. You have the second fragment, but no clear path forward.
[[Head for the Nomad lands->NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
[[Travel to the forbidden zone, seeking the third fragment->ForbiddenZoneEdge-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]

:: WastesEscape-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
You put distance between yourselves and Skybreaker. Lyra interfaces the two fragments. "The third is in a place called the GeoCore Vault, deep in the Glassplain. A dangerous journey. We need supplies and information."
[[Go to the Dustborn for help->NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]
[[Travel to the Glassplain alone->GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The Nomads are wary but respectful of your success. Moth is excited. The elder confirms the GeoCore Vault's location but warns of the Ashen Choir who guard it, believing it sacred.
[[Prepare for the journey to the Glassplain->GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
[[Remain with the Nomads for a time->NomadCaravanRest-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
:: NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
The Nomads are wary but respectful of your success. Lyra interfaces the fragments. "The third is in a place called the GeoCore Vault. A dangerous journey."
[[Begin the trek to the Glassplain->GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]
[[Remain with the Nomads for a time->NomadCaravanRest-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]
:: GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The Glassplain is a sea of fused silicate, glittering under a sickly sun. Navigation is difficult. In the distance, you see the jagged spire that marks the vault.
[[Approach the vault spire->GeoCoreVaultApproach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
:: GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
Lyra's readings help avoid unstable areas. The vault spire grows larger. She detects energy signaturesâ€”the Choir is active and alert.
[[Plan an infiltration->GeoCoreVaultInfiltration-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]
[[Attempt a direct approach->GeoCoreVaultConfrontation-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth
Lyra's readings help avoid unstable areas. The vault spire grows larger. She detects energy signaturesâ€”the Choir is active and alert. Moth navigates the terrain.
[[Plan an infiltration->GeoCoreVaultInfiltration-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth]]
[[Attempt a direct approach->GeoCoreVaultConfrontation-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth]]
:: GeoCoreVaultApproach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The entrance is a massive circular door. Choir acolytes chant nearby. There is no way past them without being seen.
[[Try to talk your way in->VaultNegotiationFail-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
[[Attack the guards->VaultFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
:: VaultNegotiationFail-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The acolytes see you as a defiler. They attack without warning, their numbers overwhelming you.
[[->Ending-Dead]]
:: VaultFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
You fight bravely, but the Choir fanatics are numerous and fight to the death. You fall under their blows.
[[->Ending-Dead]]
:: GeoCoreVaultInfiltration-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
Lyra locates a utility conduit used for maintenance. It's a tight fit, but it bypasses the main entrance, leading into the vault's lower levels.
[[Enter the conduit->GeoCoreVaultInterior-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: GeoCoreVaultConfrontation-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
You approach openly. The Choir High Priest emerges. "You seek to undo the divine ash? This is blasphemy!" He gives you a choice: leave or be sacrificed.
[[Stand your ground->VaultFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]
[[Withdraw and try infiltration->GeoCoreVaultInfiltration-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: GeoCoreVaultSecretEntrance-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth
Moth leads you to a crevice hidden by rock formations. It connects to an old air circulation system. You enter the vault unseen.
[[Navigate the ventilation system->GeoCoreVaultInterior-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: GeoCoreVaultDistraction-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth
Lyra overloads a power relay on the vault's exterior, causing a blackout and drawing the guards away. You and Moth slip inside during the confusion.
[[Enter the darkened vault->GeoCoreVaultInterior-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: GeoCoreVaultInterior-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
The vault interior is a cathedral of machinery. The third fragment is on a central terminal. But Dr. Oren Vale, the old scientist, is here, held captive by the Choir. He pleads for help.
[[Free Dr. Vale->GeoCoreVaultRescue-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithVale]]
[[Take the fragment and leave him->GeoCoreVaultFragmentTaken-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra]]

:: GeoCoreVaultInterior-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth
You find the central chamber. The third fragment glows. Dr. Vale is chained nearby, mumbling about Haven-0's true purpose. The High Priest stands guard.
[[Confront the High Priest->GeoCoreVaultFinalChoice-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale]]
[[Have Moth create a diversion while you grab the fragment->GeoCoreVaultFragmentTaken-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: GeoCoreVaultRescue-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithVale
You free Dr. Vale. He is frail but lucid. "Haven-0 is not just a purifier," he whispers. "It is a Genesis Machine. It can rebuild the biosphere... or be perverted into a weapon." You take the fragment and escape.
[[Escape the vault and plan for Haven-0->Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithVale]]

:: GeoCoreVaultFragmentTaken-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
You seize the third fragment. Alarms sound. You escape just as the Choir reinforcements arrive, but you leave Dr. Vale behind.
[[Escape to the wastes->Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra]]

:: GeoCoreVaultFragmentTaken-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth
Moth's diversion works perfectly. You grab the fragment and escape, leaving the furious Choir behind. Dr. Vale's fate is unknown.
[[Begin the final journey->Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: GeoCoreVaultFinalChoice-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale
The High Priest offers a deal: leave the fragment, and he will grant you a place in the new ashen world. Take it, and he will kill the doctor.
[[Accept his deal, abandoning the quest->Ending-Ashen]]
[[Reject his deal and fight->VaultFinalFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale]]

:: VaultFinalFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale
The fight is chaotic. Moth disarms the Priest while Lyra frees Vale. You secure the fragment. You all escape the vault, united against the final challenge.
[[Travel to Haven-0->Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale]]

:: Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra
The path to Haven-0 leads through a treacherous mountain pass. Lyra confirms the facility is ahead, sealed for centuries. The final choice looms.
[[Enter Haven-0 alone->Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra]]
[[Wait for Lyra to devise an entry strategy->Haven0Entrance-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra]]

:: Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth
The arcology is a marvel of old-world engineering, built into the mountain. Moth is in awe. The entrance is a massive airlock. The combined map fragments reveal the access code.
[[Enter Haven-0->Haven0Entrance-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithVale
Dr. Vale trembles with anticipation. "I never thought I'd return." He leads you to a hidden maintenance entrance, bypassing the main security.
[[Enter the control level->Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithVale]]

:: Haven0Approach-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale
Your group stands before the great door. Vale inputs the code. The door slides open, revealing the heart of the facility. The power is still on. The future is now.
[[Proceed to the core->Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale]]

:: Haven0Entrance-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra
The airlock opens into a silent, pristine corridor. Lyra scans ahead. "The control room is at the center. No signs of life."
[[Advance to the control room->Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra]]

:: Haven0Entrance-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth
The facility is immense. Moth looks at the clean walls and whispers, "It's like a dream." You follow the signs to the central control chamber.
[[Enter the control room->Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth]]

:: Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra
The control room is a sphere of screens and interfaces. A central console displays a schematic of the world. A choice is presented: activate the Genesis Protocol.
[[Activate the purifier->Ending-Restoration]]
[[Seize control for yourself->Ending-Dominion]]

:: Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth
Lyra studies the console. "The system is functional. We can clear the skies." Moth adds, "The Nomads could finally have a home." The choice is yours.
[[Activate the purifier for all->Ending-Restoration]]
[[Use the facility to establish a new order->Ending-Dominion]]
[[Destroy Haven-0 to prevent any faction from controlling it->Ending-Nomad]]

:: Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithVale
Dr. Vale approaches the console with reverence. "This is my life's work. We can heal the world." Lyra warns, "The Legion or Union will try to take it. We must decide its fate."
[[Let Vale activate the restoration sequence->Ending-Restoration]]
[[Claim Haven-0 as a personal fortress->Ending-Dominion]]
[[Give the access codes to the Technic Union->Ending-Technocratic]]

:: Haven0ControlRoom-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-MapFragment3-WithLyra-WithMoth-WithVale
The core hums with power. Vale explains the options: Restoration, Dominion, or surrender to a faction. Lyra and Moth look to you for the final decision.
[[Choose restoration and hope->Ending-Restoration]]
[[Choose dominion and power->Ending-Dominion]]
[[Delegate control to the Technic Union->Ending-Technocratic]]
[[Destroy the facility, preserving the balance of the wastes->Ending-Nomad]]

:: Ending-Dead
Your journey ends here, in the dust and ash. The map fragments are lost, and Haven-0 remains a legend. The wastes reclaim another soul.

:: Ending-Ashen
You accept the ash as the new truth. You join the Choir, rejecting the old world's ambition. The skies remain grey, and humanity adapts to its eternal twilight. This is peace, of a sort.

:: Ending-Restoration
The Genesis Protocol activates. Across the globe, great purifiers hum to life. The ash clouds begin to thin, and for the first time in generations, a clean blue sky is seen. The long winter is over. A new dawn begins.

:: Ending-Dominion
You seize control of Haven-0. Its technology becomes the foundation of a new empire. Your rule is absolute, a beacon of order in the chaos, but it is an order enforced by fear. The world is united under a single, iron will.

:: Ending-Technocratic
The Technic Union inherits Haven-0. Knowledge is preserved and carefully distributed. The recovery is slow, methodical, and controlled by an elite few. The future is bright, but it is not free.

:: Ending-Nomad
You overload the core, destroying Haven-0 in a controlled blast. No faction can ever wield its power. The world remains wild and free, for good and for ill. The nomads continue their wanderings, their spirit unbroken.
:: StormPathAlone
The storm is a punishing force. You wrap your scarf tight and push onward, blind and choking. After what feels like an hour, the wind subsides enough to reveal a landmark.
[[Follow the tracks->WastesAlone-MapFragment1-NearlyDead]]
:: ForbiddenZoneEdge-MapFragment1-MapFragment2
The air crackles with residual energy. Strange, twisted flora covers the landscape. A sign, barely legible, warns of "Geo-Thermal Instability." The path to the GeoCore Vault lies through this blighted land.
[[Venture into the zone->GlassplainJourney-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]
[[Seek a safer route->NomadCaravan-MapFragment1-MapFragment2]]

:: NomadCaravan-MapFragment1
You find the Dustborn caravan halted in a shallow valley. They welcome travelers, sharing water and stories. An elder examines your map fragment. "The Skybreaker ruins hold secrets, but the Steel Legion guards them fiercely. The Nomads can offer a different path."
[[Ask about the Technic Union->NomadToUnionPath-MapFragment1]]
[[Inquire about the Legion's fortress->RoadToFortress-MapFragment1]]
[[Thank them and continue alone->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]

:: NomadToUnionPath-MapFragment1-WithMoth
Moth guides you along forgotten trails. "The Union keeps to their bunkers," she says. "They trade for technology, but they are wary of outsiders." A Union scout patrol spots you, raising their weapons.
[[Attempt to parley->UnionScoutParley-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
[[Retreat and change course->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]

:: RoadToFortress-MapFragment1-WithMoth
The road to Fortress Hale is paved with intimidation. Legion checkpoints dot the route. Moth grows nervous. "They conscript the strong and discard the weak. This is a dangerous choice."
[[Approach the main gate->FortressHaleGates-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
[[Turn back before you are seen->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]

:: VaultFight-MapFragment1-MapFragment2-WithLyra
Lyra fights with shocking ferocity, using energy blasts from a concealed device. But the Choir acolytes are countless. They surround you, their chanting rising to a fever pitch. The fight is lost.
[[->Ending-Dead]]
:: FortressHaleGates-MapFragment1-WithMoth
The fortress gates are towering slabs of welded scrap. Legion sentries stare down from the walls. One shouts, "Halt! State your business!" Moth shrinks back, whispering, "They don't take kindly to nomads."
[[Claim to be a trader with information->FortressHaleInterrogation-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
[[Try to bluff your way in as a recruit->LegionRecruitment-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]

:: NomadToUnionPath-MapFragment1
The path winds towards a bunker complex hidden in a canyon. A camouflaged hatch slides open, and a Union sentry in a patched environmental suit emerges, his rifle raised. "This is restricted territory. Identify yourself."
[[Show the map fragment to gain trust->UnionScoutParley-MapFragment1]]
[[Withdraw slowly and leave->WastesAlone-MapFragment1]]

:: RoadToFortress-MapFragment1
The road is dominated by the sight of Legion land-trains, massive and intimidating. A patrol stops you. "Captain Hale seeks able bodies and useful intelligence. What do you offer?"
[[Offer your services as a scout->FortressHaleGates-MapFragment1]]
[[Claim to have information about Haven-0->LegionInformant-MapFragment1]]

:: UnionScoutParley-MapFragment1-WithMoth
The scout lowers his weapon slightly at the sight of the map fragment. "Old-world geo-data... The Union would be interested. But the exile Lyra is the true expert. Find her if you want it decrypted." He points towards Rusthaven.
[[Head to Rusthaven to find Lyra->RusthavenGates-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
:: FortressHaleGates-MapFragment1
The fortress gates are towering slabs of welded scrap. Legion sentries stare down from the walls. One shouts, "Halt! State your business!" Your presence here is a gamble.
[[Claim to be a trader with information->FortressHaleInterrogation-MapFragment1]]
[[Try to bluff your way in as a recruit->LegionRecruitment-MapFragment1]]

:: FortressHaleInterrogation-MapFragment1-WithMoth
You are led to a grim interrogation room. Captain Bronn Hale enters, his gaze piercing. "A trader? With a Nomad child in tow? Your story is thin. What information do you have that is worth my time?"
[[Mention the map fragment->LegionCapture-MapFragment1]]
[[Claim you know the location of the Technic Union's main bunker->LegionRecruitment-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]

:: LegionRecruitment-MapFragment1-WithMoth
A Legion officer scoffs. "We have no use for a courier." He points at Moth. "She will be assigned to the scullery. You will serve on the front lines. Accept this, or be ejected into the wastes."
[[Accept the terms and join the Legion->FortressHaleInduction-MapFragment1-WithMoth]]
